This patch adds a bind mount for Hobbs instance data to the docker-compose.yml.
Apply this change to .devcontainer/docker-compose.yml on the host.

--- a/.devcontainer/docker-compose.yml
+++ b/.devcontainer/docker-compose.yml
@@ -53,6 +53,8 @@
       - ${HOME}/.config/agent-sandbox/dotfiles:/home/dev/.dotfiles:ro
       # Shell customizations (optional - scripts sourced at shell startup)
       - ${HOME}/.config/agent-sandbox/shell.d:/home/dev/.config/agent-sandbox/shell.d:ro
+      # Hobbs instance data (memories, foundation, playbooks, vault)
+      - ${HOBBS_DATA:-${HOME}/.local/share/hobbs}:/home/dev/.hobbs
     working_dir: /workspace
     stdin_open: true
     tty: true

The full volumes section for the agent service should look like:

    volumes:
      # Project workspace
      - ../:/workspace
      # Prevent agent from modifying compose, policy, or devcontainer config
      - .:/workspace/.devcontainer:ro
      # Persist Claude credentials
      - claude-state:/home/dev/.claude
      # Persist shell history
      - claude-history:/commandhistory
      # Proxy CA certificate (public cert only, no private key)
      - proxy-ca:/etc/mitmproxy:ro
      # Dotfiles (optional - auto-linked into $HOME at startup)
      - ${HOME}/.config/agent-sandbox/dotfiles:/home/dev/.dotfiles:ro
      # Shell customizations (optional - scripts sourced at shell startup)
      - ${HOME}/.config/agent-sandbox/shell.d:/home/dev/.config/agent-sandbox/shell.d:ro
      # Hobbs instance data (memories, foundation, playbooks, vault)
      - ${HOBBS_DATA:-${HOME}/.local/share/hobbs}:/home/dev/.hobbs

Host-side path resolution:
  1. HOBBS_DATA if set
  2. ~/.local/share/hobbs (XDG default)

If you have a non-default XDG_DATA_HOME, set HOBBS_DATA to ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/hobbs.

Container-side path is always /home/dev/.hobbs regardless of host path.
